body.name: Patriot Memory Signature DDR3 16GB (2 x 8GB CL11 PC3-12800 (1600MHz) CAS 11 DIMM Kit with Heatshield
features: 16GB (2 x 8GB) Non-ECC Unbuffered DDR3 Memory Kit
PC3-12800 (1600MHz) Dual Data Rate, CAS 11 latency
body.description: Patriot Memory’s Signature Line DDR3 Non-ECC Unbuffered memory delivers the quality, reliability and performance expected for today’s computer needs. This 16GB kit is designed to run at PC3-12800 (1600MHz) at CAS 11 latency timings. Built using specific build-of-materials (BOMs) we ensure that every module meets and exceeds industry standards: offering you a hassle-free upgrade. We certify every component that goes into our modules, including the modules themselves, which must pass strict standards to ensure compatibility, quality and reliability. With free customer service and a lifetime warranty, Patriot Memory’s Signature memory modules are a perfect system upgrade option. FEATURES: • PC3-12800 (1600MHz) Dual Data Rate • 240-Pin Dual in-line memory module • 16GB (2 x 8GB) Non-ECC Unbuffered kit • 7.8US Refresh Interval (8192 CYCLES/64MS) • 1.5V Power Requirement • Auto and self refresh capability • PCB height: 1181(mil) • Serial Presence-Detect (SPD) • 100% Tested • RoHS Compliant

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 4 sticks for 32GB working great!
reviews.reviewText: Several months ago I bought two of these 8GB memory sticks to install next to my existing two Ballistix GB sticks. That didn't work. That's when I learned that mixing manufacturers, even if everything else is supposedly the same [aka DDR3 UDIMM 1600MHz]. I thought if I ordered the same configuration I'd be OK, but NO!So, I waited until I had some more disposable income and bought two more of the EXACT SAME memory sticks, and THAT WORKED!! I removed the Ballstix memory sticks, then installed the two new ones and powered up my PC. It ran for a few seconds, when power cycles, then ran for a few more seconds, then power cycled, etc. After few more of these, I pulled the plug and removed one of the new sticks, then powered up again. It power cycled a few more times and then POST succeeded and it made it to the Windows {10] login. After I verified that 24GB was present, I powered down and installed the re-installed the fourth memory stick, and powered back up. I don't remember if it power cycled one more time, or if it just booted up, but after that I was able to verify 32 GB!!I often run many programs at once [e.g. Firefox, DipTrace, MikroC Pro, NotePad++, PainShopPro, AdobeAcrobat, MPLAB X IPE, occasionally Adobe Illustrator -- in other words, as lot of electrical engineering stuff, and or Web Developing stuff, and/or Graphic Design stuff.] So far, with 32GB I'm not running out of memory so often [occasionally I still need to run RamMap, and Empty the Standby List -- the fact that Win 10 programs reserve so much "Stand By" memory is ridiculous, and tends to negate the advantages of a multitasking platform!]

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not easy to evaluate
reviews.reviewText: I really can't evaluate the performance of these RAM sticks because every time I put them in my motherboard, I got a bluescreen. However, I don't believe it was due to any malfunction of the RAM because I tried several other sticks with housings on them that did the same thing. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This Helped Fix My Slow Computer
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the Patriot Signature DDR3 16GB memory for my wife's computer, after looking at the onboard hardware and determining a lot of the speed issues she was having with her system was due to the old 7200rpm hard drive, and the 8GB of memory she had in the system.Replacing the hard drive with a Samsung SSD was a major help but I felt there was still a little more speed to be found for not a lot of bucks, by increasing the memory on-board.I've used Patriot Memory Modules for years and have never had anything but excellent results, so it made it easy for me to go with this memory.Patriot memory will give you lots of bang for the buck, and speed up that old slow computer!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This memory does not work in Dell 5040 computers.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for a new used computer I bought, I wanted an additional 16GB of memory added to the computer. It already had 16GB installed. When I installed it and turned on the computer, I received light codes indicating a problem. I removed all the ram and added the Patriot ram to the computer as a single and double stick, each time I received the light codes. Dell computers can be finicky with memory sticks so I did some research and was able to find a compatible brand. I decided to see if this would work in my HP Prodesk 600 G1 Tower, it works just fine. There was nothing wrong with the memory. I will be purchasing two more sticks to upgrade my HP computer to 32GB of ram. On both computers, I run virtual machines, one with Windows and one with Linux.
